                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The First Committee of the United Nations General Assembly met on January 12 from
                    3 to 5:50 p. m.; for the record, see United Nations document A/C.1/SR.423. At
                    the meeting, the Israeli Delegate introduced a draft resolution (A/C.1/647)
                    under the terms of which the First Committee would approve the principles set
                    forth in the Supplementary Report of the Cease-Fire Group (A/C.1/645) and
                    request the Secretary-General to submit them to Peking for the observations of
                    the People’s Republic of China as soon as possible. No vote was taken on the
                    draft resolution at this meeting.</p>
            </div>
